    {
      "id": "79F2RPW3TK-ogGTKajed4",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 364,
      "y": 504,
      "width": 1520.89892578125,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aC",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 124911959,
      "version": 507,
      "versionNonce": 15627671,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1768588546584,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Many organizations have VNet injected Databricks Workspaces.  These have inbound rules that prevent unknown IPs (such as the ranges that come from\nMicrosoft Hosted Pools) to talk to them.  This is because other organizations may be using that IP, thereby removing a network defense layer\n\n\nFor this reason, it is common for organizations to use self-hosted pools and use either on-premises or Azure hosted VMs to do deployments to Databricks\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Many organizations have VNet injected Databricks Workspaces.  These have inbound rules that prevent unknown IPs (such as the ranges that come from\nMicrosoft Hosted Pools) to talk to them.  This is because other organizations may be using that IP, thereby removing a network defense layer\n\n\nFor this reason, it is common for organizations to use self-hosted pools and use either on-premises or Azure hosted VMs to do deployments to Databricks\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
