      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Authentication:\nFrom an authentication perspective, SPNs are desired because they are traced to an SPN rather than\nto the user who created the PAT (as a PAT token is).  There is more setup to an SPN as it has to \nbe added to each workspace and requires Unity Catalog grants as well.  The SPN also requires\nCAN MANAGER permissions on the deployment folder.  There are some legacy APIs that don't support SPN\nso PAT may be required in some edge use cases.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Authentication:\nFrom an authentication perspective, SPNs are desired because they are traced to an SPN rather than\nto the user who created the PAT (as a PAT token is).  There is more setup to an SPN as it has to \nbe added to each workspace and requires Unity Catalog grants as well.  The SPN also requires\nCAN MANAGER permissions on the deployment folder.  There are some legacy APIs that don't support SPN\nso PAT may be required in some edge use cases.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
